Presentation

tex-templates is a collection of LaTeX classes and styles for writing
PhD dissertations, technical reports, slides and conference articles.

Slides

tex-templates provides styles for creating slides with the Beamer
tool. - “Connaissance et Intelligence Artificielle Distribuées” research
laboratory located at the Université de Technologie Belfort Montbéliard
and the Université Bourgogne Europe [download]

PhD Theses

tex-templates provides the official styles for writing a PhD thesis in
the following Universities: - Université de Technologie Belfort
Montbéliard [download part 1] [download part 2] [download part 3] -
Université Bourgogne Europe [download part 1] [download part 2]
[download part 3] - Université Marie et Louis Pasteur [download part 1]
[download part 2] [download part 3]

Examples for these PhD thesis styles may be found at:
http://www.ciad-lab.fr/

French Research Supervision Accreditation

tex-templates provides the unofficial template for preparing a French
Research Supervision Accreditation (In French: Habilitation à diriger
des recherches - HDR): - Application document for Université Bourgogne
Europe [download part 1] [download part 2] [download part 3] - HDR
report for Université Bourgogne Europe [download part 1] [download part
2] [download part 3]

Technical Reports

tex-templates provides the official template for writing the technical
reports of the CIAD Laboratory at the Université de Technologie
Belfort-Montbéliard

-   Technical or Scientific report style [download]

Conference Papers

tex-templates provides the template for the following conferences: -
IngéDoc at the Université de Technologie Belfort-Montbéliard [download]
(2016)

Installation

1.  For the reports, install the tex-upmethodology collection of classes
    and packages (also available on CTAN, and included in the major TeX
    distributions)
2.  Copy the content of the current directory inside one of your texmf
    directories, usually /usr/share/texmf/tex/latex/tex-templates or
    $HOME/.texmf on Unix operating systems.
3.  Update the LaTeX databases from the command line:

    $> mktexlsr
    $> update-updmap --quiet

